{
  "texts": [
    "Resource scheduling is another important issue for heterogeneous hardware in RANs.",
    "In traditional cloud environments, heterogeneous resource scheduling primarily relies on K8s' default scheduler.",
    "This scheduler prioritizes workload distribution at the node level based on predefined policies such as resource requests and Although this approach is effective for general resource allocation, it lacks granularity in intranode resource management.",
    "In contrast, RANs incorporate new scheduling dimensions such as energy consumption and network topology as well as enable finer-grained resource allocation within nodes.",
    "To this end, advanced scheduling mechanisms that can dynamically optimize resource usage at internode and intranode levels are required."
  ]
}